properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 29 at 3:42PM AKST until March 2 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Plan on difficult travel conditions. Total
snow accumulations of 6 to 10 inches are expected south of Carlo
Creek, with 2 to 4 inches of snow north of Carlo Creek. South
winds gusting to 50 mph along with blowing snow are expected
tonight and Sunday morning from the Denali Park Entrance to
Healy.

* WHERE...Denali.

* WHEN...9 PM today to 3 PM Monday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow is expected to develop late tonight
south of Carlo Creek and continue through Monday. South winds
gusting to 50 mph and blowing snow are expected to develop late
tonight from the Denali Park Entrance to Healy and continue
through Sunday morning. After winds decrease Sunday afternoon,
snow will develop north of Carlo Creek and winds will turn
north. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 10 inches are expected
south of Carlo Creek, with 2 to 4 inches of snow north of Carlo
Creek.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The
latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 PM AKST MONDAY
